@Stonkerzzz I was pretty much hands-off today, because this chop range doesn&#39;t do anything for me; but we closed in that &#39;indecision&#39; area of $SPY 667.  Market is getting numb to practically any news (bankruptcies, small bank loan defaults, 100% tariff talk, etc...).  Still hard to say when we get the REAL waterfall down even with this close. 
But risk-on and liquidity seems to be drying up, just by seeing speculative assets including crypto falter. 
@Shark1Mil I sold 100 shares of $UVIX on auto at $11.15 but as you can see this vol spike was short lived.  We did enter backwardation for a moment there, and VIX 20+.  All I know is that when we go under SPY 650, we will see a very decent vol spike.  I won&#39;t be adding $SVIX unless we see a move under $16. 
@User32548888 I have about 1500 shares $SOXL sitting at an average of around $33, so if I&#39;m going add more, it would have to be under $31.6.   I also have a stop loss on the whole thing around $34.  $LRCX sorta saved SMH &#39;a little bit&#39;.

$LRCX it will do even better, pick any time frame chart you want..... 

With bombs and the Devil, and the kids keep comin&#39; 
No way to breathe easy, no time to be young

